Subtitle
15
16 TO AUTHORIZE A MORTGAGOR TO RECOVER FEES
17 IN CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES UNDER THE
18 STATUTORY FORECLOSURE LAW.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
21
22 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 18, Chapter 50, Subchapter 1, is
23 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
24 18-50-118. Recovery of fees.
25 (a) A mortgagor may recover reasonable attorney's fees under this
26 subchapter if a court sets aside the statutory foreclosure sale due to a
27 mortgagee’s failure to strictly comply with any provision of § 18-50-101 et
28 seq., under § 18-50-116(d)(2)(B)(ii).
29 (b) A mortgagor shall not be awarded attorney's fees under subsection
30 (a) of this section if the:
31 (1) Mortgagor and mortgagee reach a mutual resolution of the
32 debt and corresponding foreclosure;
33 (2) Mortgagor files a petition for bankruptcy while the
34 foreclosure or any related litigation is pending;
35 (3) Mortgagee instituted the statutory foreclosure while in good
36 faith relying on a policy of title insurance that was subsequently found to
